46#ifndef NID_ED25519
47#error "Ed25519 group is not known (NID_ED25519)"

50/* OpenSSL doesn't provide direct access to key values */
51
52#define PUBPREFIXLEN 12
53
54static const unsigned char ed25519_pub_prefix[] = {
55 0x30, 0x2a, 0x30, 0x05, 0x06, 0x03, 0x2b, 0x65,
56 0x70, 0x03, 0x21, 0x00
57};
58
59static EVP_PKEY *pub_ed25519_to_ossl(const unsigned char *key)
60{
61 unsigned char buf[PUBPREFIXLEN + DNS_KEY_ED25519SIZE];
62 const unsigned char *p;
63
64 memmove(buf, ed25519_pub_prefix, PUBPREFIXLEN);
65 memmove(buf + PUBPREFIXLEN, key, DNS_KEY_ED25519SIZE);
66 p = buf;
67 return (d2i_PUBKEY(NULL, &p, PUBPREFIXLEN + DNS_KEY_ED25519SIZE));
68}
69
70static isc_result_t pub_ed25519_from_ossl(EVP_PKEY *pkey,
71 unsigned char *key)
72{
73 unsigned char buf[PUBPREFIXLEN + DNS_KEY_ED25519SIZE];
74 unsigned char *p;
75 int len;
76
77 len = i2d_PUBKEY(pkey, NULL);
78 if ((len <= DNS_KEY_ED25519SIZE) ||
79 (len > PUBPREFIXLEN + DNS_KEY_ED25519SIZE))
80 return (DST_R_OPENSSLFAILURE);
81 p = buf;
82 len = i2d_PUBKEY(pkey, &p);
83 if ((len <= DNS_KEY_ED25519SIZE) ||
84 (len > PUBPREFIXLEN + DNS_KEY_ED25519SIZE))
85 return (DST_R_OPENSSLFAILURE);
86 memmove(key, buf + len - DNS_KEY_ED25519SIZE, DNS_KEY_ED25519SIZE);
87 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
88}
89
90#define PRIVPREFIXLEN 16

93 0x30, 0x2e, 0x02, 0x01, 0x00, 0x30, 0x05, 0x06,
94 0x03, 0x2b, 0x65, 0x70, 0x04, 0x22, 0x04, 0x20
95};

277static isc_result_t
278openssleddsa_createctx(dst_key_t *key, dst_context_t *dctx) {
279 isc_buffer_t *buf = NULL;
280 isc_result_t result;
281
282 UNUSED(key);
283 REQUIRE(dctx->key->key_alg == DST_ALG_ED25519 ||
284 dctx->key->key_alg == DST_ALG_ED448);
285
286 result = isc_buffer_allocate(dctx->mctx, &buf, 64);
287 dctx->ctxdata.generic = buf;
288
289 return (result);
290}
291
292static void
293openssleddsa_destroyctx(dst_context_t *dctx) {
294 isc_buffer_t *buf = (isc_buffer_t *) dctx->ctxdata.generic;
295
296 REQUIRE(dctx->key->key_alg == DST_ALG_ED25519 ||
297 dctx->key->key_alg == DST_ALG_ED448);
298 if (buf != NULL)
299 isc_buffer_free(&buf);
300 dctx->ctxdata.generic = NULL;
301}
302
303static isc_result_t
304openssleddsa_adddata(dst_context_t *dctx, const isc_region_t *data) {
305 isc_buffer_t *buf = (isc_buffer_t *) dctx->ctxdata.generic;
306 isc_buffer_t *nbuf = NULL;
307 isc_region_t r;
308 unsigned int length;
309 isc_result_t result;
310
311 REQUIRE(dctx->key->key_alg == DST_ALG_ED25519 ||
312 dctx->key->key_alg == DST_ALG_ED448);
313
314 result = isc_buffer_copyregion(buf, data);
315 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
316 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
317
318 length = isc_buffer_length(buf) + data->length + 64;
319 result = isc_buffer_allocate(dctx->mctx, &nbuf, length);
320 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
321 return (result);
322 isc_buffer_usedregion(buf, &r);
323 (void) isc_buffer_copyregion(nbuf, &r);
324 (void) isc_buffer_copyregion(nbuf, data);
325 isc_buffer_free(&buf);
326 dctx->ctxdata.generic = nbuf;
327
328 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
329}
330
331static isc_result_t
332openssleddsa_sign(dst_context_t *dctx, isc_buffer_t *sig) {
333 isc_result_t ret;
334 dst_key_t *key = dctx->key;
335 isc_region_t tbsreg;
336 isc_region_t sigreg;
337 EVP_PKEY *pkey = key->keydata.pkey;
338 EVP_MD_CTX* ctx = EVP_MD_CTX_new();
339 isc_buffer_t *buf = (isc_buffer_t *) dctx->ctxdata.generic;
340 size_t siglen;
341
342 REQUIRE(key->key_alg == DST_ALG_ED25519 ||
343 key->key_alg == DST_ALG_ED448);
344
345 if (ctx == NULL)
346 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
347
348 if (key->key_alg == DST_ALG_ED25519)
349 siglen = DNS_SIG_ED25519SIZE;
350 else
351 siglen = DNS_SIG_ED448SIZE;
352
353 isc_buffer_availableregion(sig, &sigreg);
354 if (sigreg.length < (unsigned int) siglen)
355 DST_RET(ISC_R_NOSPACE);
356
357 isc_buffer_usedregion(buf, &tbsreg);
358
359 if (EVP_DigestSignInit(ctx, NULL, NULL, NULL, pkey) != 1) {
360 DST_RET(dst__openssl_toresult3(dctx->category,
361 "EVP_DigestSignInit",
362 ISC_R_FAILURE));
363 }
364 if (EVP_DigestSign(ctx, sigreg.base, &siglen,
365 tbsreg.base, tbsreg.length) != 1) {
366 DST_RET(dst__openssl_toresult3(dctx->category,
367 "EVP_DigestSign",
368 DST_R_SIGNFAILURE));
369 }
370 isc_buffer_add(sig, (unsigned int) siglen);
371 ret = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
372
373 err:
374 if (ctx != NULL)
375 EVP_MD_CTX_free(ctx);
376 isc_buffer_free(&buf);
377 dctx->ctxdata.generic = NULL;
378
379 return (ret);
380}
381
382static isc_result_t
383openssleddsa_verify(dst_context_t *dctx, const isc_region_t *sig) {
384 isc_result_t ret;
385 dst_key_t *key = dctx->key;
386 int status;
387 isc_region_t tbsreg;
388 EVP_PKEY *pkey = key->keydata.pkey;
389 EVP_MD_CTX* ctx = EVP_MD_CTX_new();
390 isc_buffer_t *buf = (isc_buffer_t *) dctx->ctxdata.generic;
391 unsigned int siglen = 0;
392
393 REQUIRE(key->key_alg == DST_ALG_ED25519 ||
394 key->key_alg == DST_ALG_ED448);
395
396 if (ctx == NULL)
397 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
398
399#if HAVE_OPENSSL_ED25519
400 if (key->key_alg == DST_ALG_ED25519) {
401 siglen = DNS_SIG_ED25519SIZE;
402 }
403#endif
404#if HAVE_OPENSSL_ED448
405 if (key->key_alg == DST_ALG_ED448) {
406 siglen = DNS_SIG_ED448SIZE;
407 }
408#endif
409 if (siglen == 0) {
410 return (ISC_R_NOTIMPLEMENTED);
411 }
412
413 if (sig->length != siglen)
414 return (DST_R_VERIFYFAILURE);
415
416 isc_buffer_usedregion(buf, &tbsreg);
417
418 if (EVP_DigestVerifyInit(ctx, NULL, NULL, NULL, pkey) != 1) {
419 DST_RET(dst__openssl_toresult3(dctx->category,
420 "EVP_DigestVerifyInit",
421 ISC_R_FAILURE));
422 }
423
424 status = EVP_DigestVerify(ctx, sig->base, siglen,
425 tbsreg.base, tbsreg.length);
426
427 switch (status) {
428 case 1:
429 ret = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
430 break;
431 case 0:
432 ret = dst__openssl_toresult(DST_R_VERIFYFAILURE);
433 break;
434 default:
435 ret = dst__openssl_toresult3(dctx->category,
436 "EVP_DigestVerify",
437 DST_R_VERIFYFAILURE);
438 break;
439 }
440
441 err:
442 if (ctx != NULL)
443 EVP_MD_CTX_free(ctx);
444 isc_buffer_free(&buf);
445 dctx->ctxdata.generic = NULL;
446
447 return (ret);
448}

450static bool
451openssleddsa_compare(const dst_key_t *key1, const dst_key_t *key2) {
452 int status;
453 EVP_PKEY *pkey1 = key1->keydata.pkey;
454 EVP_PKEY *pkey2 = key2->keydata.pkey;
455
456 if (pkey1 == NULL && pkey2 == NULL)
457 return (true);
458 else if (pkey1 == NULL || pkey2 == NULL)
459 return (false);
460
461 status = EVP_PKEY_cmp(pkey1, pkey2);
462 if (status == 1)
463 return (true);
464 return (false);
465}
466
467static isc_result_t
468openssleddsa_generate(dst_key_t *key, int unused, void (*callback)(int)) {
469 isc_result_t ret;
470 EVP_PKEY *pkey = NULL;
471 EVP_PKEY_CTX *ctx = NULL;
472 int nid = 0, status;
473
474 REQUIRE(key->key_alg == DST_ALG_ED25519 ||
475 key->key_alg == DST_ALG_ED448);
476 UNUSED(unused);
477 UNUSED(callback);
478
479#if HAVE_OPENSSL_ED25519
480 if (key->key_alg == DST_ALG_ED25519) {
481 nid = NID_ED25519;
482 key->key_size = DNS_KEY_ED25519SIZE;
483 }
484#endif
485#if HAVE_OPENSSL_ED448
486 if (key->key_alg == DST_ALG_ED448) {
487 nid = NID_ED448;
488 key->key_size = DNS_KEY_ED448SIZE;
489 }
490#endif
491 if (nid == 0) {
492 return (ISC_R_NOTIMPLEMENTED);
493 }
494
495 ctx = EVP_PKEY_CTX_new_id(nid, NULL);
496 if (ctx == NULL)
497 return (dst__openssl_toresult2("EVP_PKEY_CTX_new_id",
498 DST_R_OPENSSLFAILURE));
499
500 status = EVP_PKEY_keygen_init(ctx);
501 if (status != 1)
502 DST_RET (dst__openssl_toresult2("EVP_PKEY_keygen_init",
503 DST_R_OPENSSLFAILURE));
504
505 status = EVP_PKEY_keygen(ctx, &pkey);
506 if (status != 1)
507 DST_RET (dst__openssl_toresult2("EVP_PKEY_keygen",
508 DST_R_OPENSSLFAILURE));
509
510 key->keydata.pkey = pkey;
511 ret = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
512
513 err:
514 if (ctx != NULL)
515 EVP_PKEY_CTX_free(ctx);
516 return (ret);
517}

519static bool
520openssleddsa_isprivate(const dst_key_t *key) {
521 EVP_PKEY *pkey = key->keydata.pkey;
522 int len;
523 unsigned long err;
524
525 if (pkey == NULL)
526 return (false);
527
528 len = i2d_PrivateKey(pkey, NULL);
529 if (len > 0)
530 return (true);
531 /* can check if first error is EC_R_INVALID_PRIVATE_KEY */
532 while ((err = ERR_get_error()) != 0)
533 /**/;
534
535 return (false);
536}

538static void
539openssleddsa_destroy(dst_key_t *key) {
540 EVP_PKEY *pkey = key->keydata.pkey;
541
542 EVP_PKEY_free(pkey);
543 key->keydata.pkey = NULL;
544}

546static isc_result_t
547openssleddsa_todns(const dst_key_t *key, isc_buffer_t *data) {
548 EVP_PKEY *pkey = key->keydata.pkey;
549 isc_region_t r;
550 isc_result_t result;
551
552 REQUIRE(pkey != NULL);
553
554 pkey = key->keydata.pkey;
555 switch (key->key_alg) {
556 case DST_ALG_ED25519:
557 isc_buffer_availableregion(data, &r);
558 if (r.length < DNS_KEY_ED25519SIZE)
559 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
560 result = pub_ed25519_from_ossl(pkey, r.base);
561 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
562 isc_buffer_add(data, DNS_KEY_ED25519SIZE);
563 return (result);
564 case DST_ALG_ED448:
565 isc_buffer_availableregion(data, &r);
566 if (r.length < DNS_KEY_ED448SIZE)
567 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
568 result = pub_ed448_from_ossl(pkey, r.base);
569 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
570 isc_buffer_add(data, DNS_KEY_ED448SIZE);
571 return (result);
572 default:
573 INSIST(0);
574 ISC_UNREACHABLE();
575 }
576}
577
578static isc_result_t
579openssleddsa_fromdns(dst_key_t *key, isc_buffer_t *data) {
580 EVP_PKEY *pkey;
581 isc_region_t r;
582 unsigned int len;
583
584 REQUIRE(key->key_alg == DST_ALG_ED25519 ||
585 key->key_alg == DST_ALG_ED448);
586
587 isc_buffer_remainingregion(data, &r);
588 if (r.length == 0)
589 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
590 if (key->key_alg == DST_ALG_ED25519) {
591 len = DNS_KEY_ED25519SIZE;
592 if (r.length < len)
593 return (DST_R_INVALIDPUBLICKEY);
594 pkey = pub_ed25519_to_ossl(r.base);
595 } else {
596 len = DNS_KEY_ED448SIZE;
597 if (r.length < len)
598 return (DST_R_INVALIDPUBLICKEY);
599 pkey = pub_ed448_to_ossl(r.base);
600 }
601 if (pkey == NULL)
602 return (dst__openssl_toresult(ISC_R_FAILURE));
603 isc_buffer_forward(data, len);
604 key->keydata.pkey = pkey;
605 key->key_size = len;
606 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
607}
608
609static isc_result_t
610openssleddsa_tofile(const dst_key_t *key, const char *directory) {
611 isc_result_t ret;
612 EVP_PKEY *pkey;
613 dst_private_t priv;
614 unsigned char *buf = NULL;
615 unsigned int len;
616
617 REQUIRE(key->key_alg == DST_ALG_ED25519 ||
618 key->key_alg == DST_ALG_ED448);
619
620 if (key->keydata.pkey == NULL)
621 return (DST_R_NULLKEY);
622
623 if (key->external) {
624 priv.nelements = 0;
625 return (dst__privstruct_writefile(key, &priv, directory));
626 }
627
628 pkey = key->keydata.pkey;
629 if (key->key_alg == DST_ALG_ED25519) {
630 len = DNS_KEY_ED25519SIZE;
631 buf = isc_mem_get(key->mctx, len);
632 if (buf == NULL)
633 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
634 priv.elements[0].tag = TAG_EDDSA_PRIVATEKEY;
635 priv.elements[0].length = len;
636 ret = priv_ed25519_from_ossl(pkey, buf);
637 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
638 DST_RET (dst__openssl_toresult(ret));
639 priv.elements[0].data = buf;
640 priv.nelements = 1;
641 ret = dst__privstruct_writefile(key, &priv, directory);
642 } else {
643 len = DNS_KEY_ED448SIZE;
644 buf = isc_mem_get(key->mctx, len);
645 if (buf == NULL)
646 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
647 priv.elements[0].tag = TAG_EDDSA_PRIVATEKEY;
648 priv.elements[0].length = len;
649 ret = priv_ed448_from_ossl(pkey, buf);
650 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
651 DST_RET (dst__openssl_toresult(ret));
652 priv.elements[0].data = buf;
653 priv.nelements = 1;
654 ret = dst__privstruct_writefile(key, &priv, directory);
655 }
656
657 err:
658 if (buf != NULL)
659 isc_mem_put(key->mctx, buf, len);
660 return (ret);
661}
662
663static isc_result_t
664eddsa_check(EVP_PKEY *privkey, dst_key_t *pub)
665{
666 EVP_PKEY *pkey;
667
668 if (pub == NULL)
669 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
670 pkey = pub->keydata.pkey;
671 if (pkey == NULL)
672 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
673 if (EVP_PKEY_cmp(privkey, pkey) == 1)
674 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
675 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
676}
677
678static isc_result_t
679openssleddsa_parse(dst_key_t *key, isc_lex_t *lexer, dst_key_t *pub) {
680 dst_private_t priv;
681 isc_result_t ret;
682 EVP_PKEY *pkey = NULL;
683 unsigned int len;
684 isc_mem_t *mctx = key->mctx;
685
686 REQUIRE(key->key_alg == DST_ALG_ED25519 ||
687 key->key_alg == DST_ALG_ED448);
688
689 /* read private key file */
690 ret = dst__privstruct_parse(key, DST_ALG_ED25519, lexer, mctx, &priv);
691 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
692 goto err;
693
694 if (key->external) {
695 if (priv.nelements != 0)
696 DST_RET(DST_R_INVALIDPRIVATEKEY);
697 if (pub == NULL)
698 DST_RET(DST_R_INVALIDPRIVATEKEY);
699 key->keydata.pkey = pub->keydata.pkey;
700 pub->keydata.pkey = NULL;
701 dst__privstruct_free(&priv, mctx);
702 isc_safe_memwipe(&priv, sizeof(priv));
703 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
704 }
705
706 if (key->key_alg == DST_ALG_ED25519) {
707 len = DNS_KEY_ED25519SIZE;
708 if (priv.elements[0].length < len)
709 DST_RET(DST_R_INVALIDPRIVATEKEY);
710 pkey = priv_ed25519_to_ossl(priv.elements[0].data);
711 } else {
712 len = DNS_KEY_ED448SIZE;
713 if (priv.elements[0].length < len)
714 DST_RET(DST_R_INVALIDPRIVATEKEY);
715 pkey = priv_ed448_to_ossl(priv.elements[0].data);
716 }
717 if (pkey == NULL)
718 DST_RET (dst__openssl_toresult(DST_R_OPENSSLFAILURE));
719 if (eddsa_check(pkey, pub) != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
720 EVP_PKEY_free(pkey);
721 DST_RET(DST_R_INVALIDPRIVATEKEY);
722 }
723 key->keydata.pkey = pkey;
724 key->key_size = len;
725 ret = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
726
727 err:
728 dst__privstruct_free(&priv, mctx);
729 isc_safe_memwipe(&priv, sizeof(priv));
730 return (ret);
731}

734 openssleddsa_createctx,
735 NULL, /*%< createctx2 */
736 openssleddsa_destroyctx,
737 openssleddsa_adddata,
738 openssleddsa_sign,
739 openssleddsa_verify,
740 NULL, /*%< verify2 */
741 NULL, /*%< computesecret */
742 openssleddsa_compare,

744 openssleddsa_generate,

746 openssleddsa_destroy,
747 openssleddsa_todns,

749 openssleddsa_tofile,

751 NULL, /*%< cleanup */

753 NULL, /*%< dump */
754 NULL, /*%< restore */

757isc_result_t
758dst__openssleddsa_init(dst_func_t **funcp) {
759 REQUIRE(funcp != NULL);
760 if (*funcp == NULL)
761 *funcp = &openssleddsa_functions;
762 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
763}
